1
00:00:00,358 --> 00:00:04,882
♪A little bit sorry for my love for you♪

2
00:00:04,882 --> 00:00:10,386
♪Sorry, I was a little late♪

3
00:00:10,386 --> 00:00:16,814
♪I really want the unconscious longing
to appear faster♪

4
00:00:16,814 --> 00:00:21,294
♪Can I get closer
and hear you say "I do" once more♪

5
00:00:21,294 --> 00:00:25,742
♪Holding hands, the scenery
in midsummer is a new journey♪

6
00:00:25,742 --> 00:00:30,653
♪The chapters of a fairy tale
are performed one after another♪

7
00:00:30,653 --> 00:00:34,702
♪The promised moment
will definitely not be forgotten♪

8
00:00:34,702 --> 00:00:39,237
♪Can I get closer and listen to
the frequency of your heartbeat♪

9
00:00:39,237 --> 00:00:43,534
♪Start the countdown 4321,
a new scenery♪

10
00:00:43,534 --> 00:00:48,299
♪I want to see all the scenes about you♪

11
00:00:48,299 --> 00:00:51,790
♪No need to miss you anymore♪

12
00:00:51,790 --> 00:00:55,470
♪Right by your side♪

13
00:00:57,116 --> 00:01:00,494
=Jin Secretary=

14
00:01:00,494 --> 00:01:03,182
=Episode 10=

15
00:01:03,400 --> 00:01:05,900
Do you think we would choose
to partner with such a company?

16
00:01:22,933 --> 00:01:24,766
The masked man stole my phone

17
00:01:25,600 --> 00:01:27,033
and inserted a USB stick into it.

18
00:01:28,433 --> 00:01:29,733
Help me figure out what's going on.

19
00:01:29,966 --> 00:01:31,104
Okay.

20
00:01:33,766 --> 00:01:35,866
Mr. Zeng, we've found out

21
00:01:35,866 --> 00:01:39,766
that the USB inserted in your phone
had the bills of WE Beauty Group.

22
00:01:40,000 --> 00:01:44,233
It's likely that they stole your phone
to avoid exposing their identity

23
00:01:44,233 --> 00:01:45,733
through network transmission
or delivery.

24
00:01:50,100 --> 00:01:51,400
Okay.

25
00:01:58,633 --> 00:01:59,899
Hello.

26
00:02:00,000 --> 00:02:01,733
This is a top-level internal meeting.

27
00:02:02,000 --> 00:02:03,600
It's not a place for a secretary.

28
00:02:06,866 --> 00:02:09,166
I'll stay wherever Mr. Lan is.

29
00:02:09,233 --> 00:02:11,033
If you can't stand it,

30
00:02:11,100 --> 00:02:13,433
it means you're not suited to be here.

31
00:02:14,633 --> 00:02:17,433
What do you mean?
Do you know who I am?

32
00:02:17,533 --> 00:02:18,833
Aren't you afraid I'll...

33
00:02:19,100 --> 00:02:22,100
Afraid? Afraid of what?

34
00:02:22,133 --> 00:02:24,033
Afraid of having your cover blown?

35
00:02:25,400 --> 00:02:27,700
As for what happened
in the meeting just now,

36
00:02:27,733 --> 00:02:31,799
I believe everyone here
is responsible, right?

37
00:02:34,233 --> 00:02:35,999
It's the accounts.

38
00:02:37,100 --> 00:02:39,600
It's because there was a problem
with our company's accounts

39
00:02:39,766 --> 00:02:42,833
that Mr. Zeng refused to cooperate.

40
00:02:43,533 --> 00:02:44,800
That's ridiculous.

41
00:02:45,033 --> 00:02:47,800
What would a secretary know? Goodness.

42
00:02:47,966 --> 00:02:49,433
Okay, everyone, calm down.

43
00:02:50,066 --> 00:02:50,866
Miss Jin,

44
00:02:51,400 --> 00:02:54,500
what you mentioned is very serious.

45
00:02:54,533 --> 00:02:58,166
Do you know how big a problem and risk
it implies for our company?

46
00:02:58,266 --> 00:02:59,866
Of course I know.

47
00:02:59,900 --> 00:03:02,400
I am more surprised than anyone here.

48
00:03:02,400 --> 00:03:04,100
Because this is

49
00:03:04,100 --> 00:03:05,700
what Mr. Zeng told me in person.

50
00:03:13,066 --> 00:03:17,133
Alright, that's it. Dismiss.

51
00:03:23,233 --> 00:03:25,600
I will handle this matter.

52
00:03:42,600 --> 00:03:46,800
Miss Jin, cancel
all of today's schedule.

53
00:03:47,000 --> 00:03:49,866
Without my permission,
no one is allowed to come in.

54
00:03:49,866 --> 00:03:51,166
Mr. Lan, today...

55
00:03:51,200 --> 00:03:53,366
Alright, you can leave.

56
00:04:13,300 --> 00:04:15,666
Sis, how is Mr. Lan doing now?

57
00:04:15,733 --> 00:04:17,366
Has he taken a big hit?

58
00:04:18,200 --> 00:04:19,233
I'm not sure.

59
00:04:20,266 --> 00:04:22,833
He has locked himself in his office.

60
00:04:22,866 --> 00:04:25,133
Sis, what should we do about this?

61
00:04:27,800 --> 00:04:29,833
It's

62
00:04:29,833 --> 00:04:31,766
probably not that simple.

63
00:04:34,866 --> 00:04:39,733
Right now, only you are by his side.
You must help him.

64
00:04:53,733 --> 00:04:57,266
Let's just do some research.
As much as we can.

65
00:04:57,333 --> 00:05:00,799
After all, we don't want you
to lose the job.

66
00:05:00,833 --> 00:05:02,599
If I lose the job,
I can find another one.

67
00:05:02,600 --> 00:05:03,500
Lan Chen...

68
00:05:09,600 --> 00:05:12,400
He helped us. And...

69
00:05:14,833 --> 00:05:16,599
He is the man you like.

70
00:05:20,800 --> 00:05:22,600
So let's help him.

71
00:05:42,997 --> 00:05:44,367
(Financial Analysis Report)

72
00:05:56,992 --> 00:06:00,000
(CFO Zuo Jiazhang)

73
00:06:04,000 --> 00:06:05,500
Xi'en, wake up.

74
00:06:05,766 --> 00:06:08,200
Make a real market research report.

75
00:06:25,666 --> 00:06:26,466
Mr. Lan.

76
00:06:27,866 --> 00:06:31,633
Thank you for showing up the night
Gu came to my house to make trouble.

77
00:06:33,266 --> 00:06:34,699
Why bring this up all of a sudden?

78
00:06:35,633 --> 00:06:37,900
Nothing. Just suddenly remembered it.

79
00:06:37,966 --> 00:06:40,533
So I've prepared a gift for you

80
00:06:41,833 --> 00:06:42,766
as a token of gratitude.

81
00:06:45,100 --> 00:06:46,366
This is...?

82
00:06:53,600 --> 00:06:56,900
A design sketch by my favorite
fashion designer, Yifu Dashienski,

83
00:06:57,000 --> 00:06:58,066
and it's autographed.

84
00:06:59,466 --> 00:07:01,933
Miss Jin, where did you get this?

85
00:07:02,066 --> 00:07:04,466
A friend overseas helped me get it.

86
00:07:04,833 --> 00:07:06,399
You've been abroad?

87
00:07:06,466 --> 00:07:09,166
Of course, I have.
I competed in leagues overseas.

88
00:07:11,233 --> 00:07:16,966
I participated in the College Technology
Entrepreneurship Competition overseas.

89
00:07:20,900 --> 00:07:23,500
Why did you know I love fashion design?

90
00:07:23,633 --> 00:07:27,833
Even a blind man would know.
All your books are about fashion design.

91
00:07:34,500 --> 00:07:35,300
Miss Jin,

92
00:07:37,133 --> 00:07:37,933
thank you.

93
00:07:38,866 --> 00:07:40,133
I feel much better now.

94
00:07:41,800 --> 00:07:45,800
Actually, you don't have to
be so stressed out.

95
00:07:48,899 --> 00:07:53,733
The company had a huge financial problem
during this period.

96
00:07:53,733 --> 00:07:56,433
If we can't cooperate
with Lihuai International,

97
00:07:56,500 --> 00:07:58,866
we may go bankrupt at any time.

98
00:08:01,633 --> 00:08:05,599
If the company goes bankrupt,
I can get a new job.

99
00:08:05,600 --> 00:08:07,433
And I won't be under such high pressure.

100
00:08:08,700 --> 00:08:10,266
You'll be free.

101
00:08:11,100 --> 00:08:13,100
But have you ever thought about

102
00:08:13,100 --> 00:08:16,000
how many families a company supports?

103
00:08:16,000 --> 00:08:18,000
If the company goes down,

104
00:08:18,000 --> 00:08:19,033
what about them?

105
00:08:24,866 --> 00:08:28,233
Actually, ever since
I joined the company, I knew

106
00:08:28,233 --> 00:08:30,166
Mei Xiangfa is influential.

107
00:08:30,200 --> 00:08:34,400
Bu Zhengjing, Zuo Jiazhang,
and Liang Liangqiang are all his men.

108
00:08:36,066 --> 00:08:38,433
We can't fire them for now.

109
00:08:38,566 --> 00:08:40,499
Removing them will cause pain.

110
00:08:40,666 --> 00:08:44,899
We need to take it slow.
Reform needs time.

111
00:08:47,400 --> 00:08:49,266
I will do my best to help you.

112
00:08:49,366 --> 00:08:52,699
But I hope that
after you complete these missions,

113
00:08:52,800 --> 00:08:55,633
you can do something
you're really interested in.

114
00:08:58,700 --> 00:09:00,866
Okay, I promise you.

115
00:09:02,950 --> 00:09:06,431
♪Stars fall into my eyes,
and you fall into my heart♪

116
00:09:06,431 --> 00:09:10,552
♪I make a wish foolishly,
but actually, you are the shooting star♪

117
00:09:10,552 --> 00:09:12,248
♪Open my secret♪

118
00:09:12,248 --> 00:09:18,296
♪I hope you find
all the tenderness hidden for you♪

119
00:09:19,686 --> 00:09:24,208
♪I pass through the crowd with you♪

120
00:09:27,238 --> 00:09:32,199
♪As if we have a tacit understanding,
attracting each other♪

121
00:09:35,248 --> 00:09:41,072
♪When the loneliness cracks,
warmth seeps in♪

122
00:09:41,072 --> 00:09:48,542
♪You come with light,
shining into my heart♪

123
00:09:48,542 --> 00:09:52,023
♪Stars fall into my eyes,
and you fall into my heart♪

124
00:09:52,023 --> 00:09:56,144
♪I make a wish foolishly,
but actually, you are the shooting star♪

125
00:09:56,144 --> 00:09:57,840
♪Open my secret♪

126
00:09:57,840 --> 00:10:03,888
♪I hope you find
all the tenderness hidden for you♪

127
00:10:03,888 --> 00:10:07,760
♪Sinking into your love,
I want to sink deeper♪

128
00:10:07,760 --> 00:10:12,266
♪With each breath,
I can feel the sweetness♪

129
00:10:12,266 --> 00:10:20,976
♪Two lonely islands meet,
and it's the gift of fate♪
